 1. Business Understanding Summary

 The system replaces manual first-pass loan review with a four-agent AI pipeline backed by a deterministic rule engine. Every
 decision is one of: Approved, Rejected, or Requires Manual Review.

 Two governing constraints:
 1. All arithmetic (DTI, risk scores, thresholds) is computed by core/rules.py — Claude never does math.
 2. Borderline and anomalous cases are routed to manual review rather than auto-rejected, supporting ECOA/fair-lending
 obligations.

 Claude is invoked solely for: reasoning (Agent B), key_decision_factors + explanation (Agent C), and summary (Agent D). Every
 agent output carries a traceable case_id, UTC timestamp, and full JSON audit trail.

